summary:
The Security Council, recalling previous resolutions on Côte d'Ivoire and Liberia, considered the recommendations for a revised mandate of the United Nations Operation in Côte d'Ivoire (UNOCI) in the Secretary-General's report of 20 May 2010. Determining the situation in Côte d'Ivoire continues to threaten international peace and security, it: 
1. Extends the mandate of UNOCI, as determined in resolution 1739 (2007), until 30 June 2010; 
2. Extends the authorization for French forces to support UNOCI, within their deployment and capabilities, until 30 June 2010; 
3. Decides to remain actively seized of the matter.
